(13, 1, 'Earthquakes', '<div class="step-title">During an Earthquake</div>\r\n<table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td height="28" class="bullet_bg">Drop, cover and hold. Move only as far as necessary to reach a safe place.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td height="28" class="bullet_bg">If indoors, stay there. It  is safer to stay indoors until the shaking stops than it is safe to  exit. When going outdoors, move quickly away from the building to  prevent injury from falling debris.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td height="28" class="bullet_bg">If outdoors, find a spot  away from buildings, trees, streetlights and power lines and over  passes. Drop to the ground and stay there until the shaking stops.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td height="28" class="bullet_bg">If in a vehicle, pull over at a clear location and stop. Stay in the vehicle with seatbelt fastened until the shaking stops.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td height="28" class="bullet_bg">If in a high rise  building, expect the fire alarms and sprinkler systems to go off during  an earthquake. Check for and extinguish small fires. DO NOT use  elevators.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td height="28" class="bullet_bg">If in a coastal area, move to higher ground. Earthquakes often generate tsunamis.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td height="28" class="bullet_bg">If in a mountainous area  or near unstable slopes or cliffs, be alert for falling rock and other  debris that could be loosened by the eathquake. Also, watch for  landslides that could be triggered by the earthquake.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>', '2014-02-10 21:41:54', 1),
