(21, 67, 'Bomb Threats', '<p><b>Date Call Received:___________  Time Call Was Received:________</b></p>\r\n<p><b>Time Call Ended:____________</b></p>\r\n<p><b>Employee Taking The Call:_____________________________________</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 1: DO NOT TRANSFER THE CALL.</p>\r\n<p>Step 2: If you have a display phone, note any information shown.</p>\r\n<p>Step 3: Use the pre-determined signal to alert co-workers and of the treat. They will notify police.</p>\r\n<p>Step 4: Do not argue with the caller.</p>\r\n<p>Step 5: Keep the caller on the phone as long as possible. Doing so could allow police to trace the call.</p>\r\n<p>Step 6: Record details of the conversation as noted below immediately following caller hanging up.</p>\r\n<p><b>Ask the following questions:</b></p>\r\n<p>When will the bomb explode?______________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>Where is it now?________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>What does it look it?_____________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>What kind of bomb is it?__________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>What will cause it to explode?______________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>Why are you doing this?__________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>What would you like me to do?_____________________________________________</p>\r\n<p><b>Note the follow details:</b></p>\r\n<p>Male or Female Voice:_____________ Age:__________</p>\r\n<p>Emotional State: ________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>Speech pattern and/or accent:_____________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>Background noises:_____________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>Exact words of the caller:_________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>Additional Comments:____________________________________________________</p>\r\n', '2014-02-14 17:54:33', 1),
(22, 67, 'Earthquakes', '<p><u><b>During an Earthquake:</b></u></p>\r\n<p>Drop, cover and hold. Move only as far as necessary to reach a safe place.</p>\r\n<p><u><b>If indoors,</b></u> stay there. It is safer to stay indoors until the shaking stops and it is safe to exit. When going outdoors, move quickly away from the building to prevent injury from falling debris.</p>\r\n<p><u><b>If outdoors,</b></u> find a spot away from buildings, trees, streetlights and power lines and over passes. Drop to the ground and stay there until the shaking stops.</p>\r\n<p><u><b>If in a vehicle,</b></u> pull over at a clear location and stop. Stay in the vehicle with seatbelt fastened until the shaking stops.</p>\r\n<p><u><b>If in a high-rise building,</b></u> expect the fire alarms and sprinkler systems to go off during an earthquake. Check for and extinguish small fires. DO NOT use elevators.</p>\r\n<p><u><b>If in a coastal area,</b></u> move to higher ground. Earthquakes often generate tsunamis.</p>\r\n<p><u><b>If in a mountainous area or near unstable slopes or cliffs,</b></u> be alert for falling rock and other debris that could be loosened by the earthquake. Also, watch for landslides that could be triggered by the earthquake.</p>\r\n<p><u><b>Company Recommendations:</b></u></p>\r\n<p>_______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>________________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>________________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 19:39:15', 1),
(23, 67, 'Fires', '<p><u><b>When Fire Breaks Out</b></u></p>\r\n<p>-Regardless of the size of the fire, ALWAYS contact the fire department. Never assume that someone else has called. Then contact the Team Leader to apprise him/her of the situation.</p>\r\n<p>-Team Leader determines if emergency plan activation is necessary.</p>\r\n<p>-If plan is activated, ALL operations shut down to deal with the fire.</p>\r\n<p>-Response Team goes into action.</p>\r\n<p>-Assist emergency fire and police personnel and other emergency management personnel when asked.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>If you are in the building when the fire breaks out and are able to get out:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-Stay calm and do not run because this will fan the flames.</p>\r\n<p>-During your exit, keep in contact with personnel with your two-way radio or cell phone.</p>\r\n<p>-Close as many doors in the hallway or stairwells as possible without endangering yourself.</p>\r\n<p>-Get down on the floor, crawl and use the wall to feel your way out.</p>\r\n<p>-Use handrails as you descend stairs.</p>\r\n<p>-Before opening any doors, test them to see if they are hot by placing the back of your hand carefully on the door. If hot, try to find another way out. If not, slowly open the door.</p>\r\n<p>-If your clothes catch fire, STOP, DROP, ROLL. Cover your face with your hands.</p>\r\n<p>-When outside, move away from the building.</p>\r\n<p><u><b>If you are unable to get out of the building:</b></u></p>\r\n<p>-Stay calm. Do not run. This fans the flames.</p>\r\n<p>-Find a room with a window.</p>\r\n<p>-Use two-way radio or cell phone to notify personnel of your exact location.</p>\r\n<p>-If in a room, open the window to allow air in. Wave something brightly colored out the window.</p>\r\n<p>-Make certain the doors in the room are closed and seal the cracks under the door.</p>\r\n<p>-Cover vents with rags, clothing, towels, newspapers or anything you can find that will do the job.</p>\r\n<p>-If possible use a wet cloth to breath into.</p>\r\n<p>-DO NOT USE ELEVATORS.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 19:58:18', 1),
(24, 67, 'Floods', '<p><b><u>If a Flood is Imminent</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-Contact your immediate supervisor to alert them to the impending situation.</p>\r\n<p>-Team Leader meets with On-Site Emergency Team to review employee assignments.</p>\r\n<p>-Notify residents of impending situation. Bullhorn, knocking on doors, door hangers, telephone calls. Instruct them to remove all belonging from patios and balconies.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>During a Flood</u></b></p>\r\n<p>If you were unable to move to higher ground and are in a building surrounding by flood waters:</p>\r\n<p>-DO NOT ATTEMPT AN ESCAPE. Use your radio or cell phone and call the Team Leader to affirm your location.</p>\r\n<p>-Use no open lflames for there may be escaped gas from ruptured lines.</p>\r\n<p>-Shut down power to the buildings.</p>\r\n<p>-In the event flood waters begin entering power source areas try to relocate equipment to higher floors.</p>\r\n<p>Use alternate power sources if they exist.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>If you are in a vehicle</u></b> and water starts to surround the vehicle, DO NOT attempt to drive through the water. Abandon your car and move to higher ground <b><u>immediately</u>.</b></p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 20:11:15', 1),
(25, 67, 'Hurricanes', '<p><b><u>If a Hurricane is Imminent</b></u></p>\r\n<p>-Contact your immediate supervisor and the corporate office and alert them to the impending situation.</p>\r\n<p>-Team Leader meets with On-Site Emergency Team to review individual responsiblities of each team member.</p>\r\n<p>-Activate the Response Team.</p>\r\n<p>-Notify residents of impending situation. Bullhorn, knocking on doors, door hangers, and telephone calls. Instruct them to remove all belongings from patios and balconies.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Hurricane WATCH</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-A Hurricane Watch is issued when there is a threat of hurricane conditions within 24-36 horus.</p>\r\n<p>-Follow company procedures.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>During a Hurricane</b></u></p>\r\n<p>-Refrain from using cell phones, telephones, and radios. Instead send text messages.</p>\r\n<p>-See that all team members are accounted once they are gathered in the pre-designated area. In this area should be the apartment community''s disaster supplies kit and first aid kit.</p>\r\n<p>-Listen to radio for updated information and continuall check for text messages.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</b></u></p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_______________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 20:20:04', 1),
(26, 67, 'Power Outages', '<p><b><u>Safety Tips in the Event of Power Failure</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-Only use a flashlight for emergency lighting. Never use candles</p>\r\n<p>-Turn off electrical equipment you were using when the power went out.</p>\r\n<p>-Do not run a generator inside a building or maintenance shop.</p>\r\n<p>-Do not run a generator inside a building or maintenance shop.</p>\r\n<p>-If you use a generator, connect the equipment you want to power directly to the outlets on the generator. Do not connect a generator to a home''s electrical system.</p>\r\n<p>-Listen to local radio and television for updated information.</p>\r\n<p>-Stay alert for down lines. If you see a downed power line, let utility company know immediately.</p>\r\n<p>-Stay away from any downed line. Assume it''s live and dangerous, and warn children to stay away and notify resident. Downed lines do not always spark, burn or arc. Never assume any downed wire is harmless. Objects such as metal fences and water in contact with power lines could be energized and lethal. STAY AWAY.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n', '2014-02-14 20:33:29', 1),
(27, 67, 'Severe Storm', '<p><b><u>During a Thunderstorm:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-Avoid water sources such as pools and ponds, and get off pool decks.</p>\r\n<p>-The telephone should not be used because electricity from lighting can also travel through phone lines.</p>\r\n<p>-Turn off air conditioning. This action can eliminate the risk of damage from surges that accompany lighting strikes in close proximity to the the home.</p>\r\n<p>-Seek shelter in an enclosed structure away from windows.</p>\r\n<p>-If you cannot reach a permanent shelter, take shelter in a vehicle. Keep all windows closed and do not touch anything metal.</p>\r\n<p>-As a last resort, go to a low-lying area, away from trees, poles and metal objects. Squat low to the ground making the smallest target possible while minimizing contact with the ground. Place your hands on your knees with your head between them. Make as small a target as possible. <u>DO NOT lie flat on the ground.</u></p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 20:40:10', 1),
(28, 67, 'Work Place Violence', '<p>Although no definite strategy will ever be appropriate for all workplace violence, follow company general prodcedures for workplace violence. Workplace violence includes any physical assualt, threatening behavior, disorderly conduct, any sexual assault, destruction of property, verbal abuse, harassment, telephone or email misuse, stalking, in any location where any employee performs any work-related duty.</p>\r\n<p><u><strong>Preventative Measures Include:</strong></u></p>\r\n<p>-If possible never work alone.</p>\r\n<p>-Establish a code word to be used when in a potential violent situation.</p>\r\n<p>-Always let someone know where you are going and who you are with.</p>\r\n<p>-Carry a cell phone or two-way radio.</p>\r\n<p>-Follow your intuition.</p>\r\n<p>-Learn how to deescalate a distraught person. Be sincere and professional, remain calm, listen, speak in a soft voice, be honest about your limitations, don''t argue, call for help.</p>\r\n<p>-Install good external lighting outside office and maintence shop areas.</p>\r\n<p>-Consider installing closed-circuit cameras, alarms, two-way mirrors, and card access systems.</p>\r\n<p>-Change-up work practices and staffing patterns.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 20:47:34', 1),
(29, 67, 'Terrorism', '<p>Wherever you are, beware of your surrounding. The very nature of terrorism suggests there may be a little to no warning. Always be alert to suspicious activity and conspicuous or unusual behavior.</p>\r\n<p><u><strong>Acts of terrorism include but are not limited to:</strong></u></p>\r\n<p>-Assassinations</p>\r\n<p>-Kidnappings</p>\r\n<p>-Hijackings</p>\r\n<p>-Bomb scares and bombings</p>\r\n<p>-Dirty bombs</p>\r\n<p>-Cyber attacks (computer based)</p>\r\n<p>-Chemical attacks</p>\r\n<p>-Biological weapons</p>\r\n<p>-Nuclear weapons</p>\r\n<p>-Utility loss or disruption</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 20:53:32', 1),
(30, 67, 'Tornadoes', '<p><b><u>Signs to Look For:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-Most obvious are high winds and very large hail.</p>\r\n<p>-Sounds like a train is coming.</p>\r\n<p>-Tornadoes can be wrapped in heavy rain, which may limit visibility. But because tornadoes are associated with powerful updrafts, rain does not always fall in or near tornadoes.</p>\r\n<p>-Tornadoes may appear nearly transparent until they pick up dust and debris. In this case debris such as braches or leaves being pulled upwards is a clue.</p>\r\n<p>-An obvious funnel-shaped cloud that is rotating.</p>\r\n<p>-Sickly greenish or greenish black sky.</p>\r\n<p>-A strange quiet that occurs within or shortly after a thunderstorm.</p>\r\n<p>-Cloud moving very fast.</p>\r\n<p>-Debris could be dropping from the sky.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>If Outdoors:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-If possible, get inside a building.</p>\r\n<p>-If shelter is not available or there is no time to get indoors, lie in a ditch or low-lying area or crouch near a strong building. Be aware of the potential for flooding.</p>\r\n<p>-Use arms to protect head and neck.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>If in a Vehicle:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-Never try to out-drive a tornado in a car or truck.</p>\r\n<p>-Get out of the vehicle immediately and take shelter in a nearby building.</p>\r\n<p>-If there is no time to get indoors, get out of the vehicle and lie in a ditch or low-lying area away from the vehicle.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n', '2014-02-14 21:04:49', 1),
(31, 67, 'Resident Death', '<p><b><u>If you find a body:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-Leave the apartment without disturbing the body or other belongings.</p>\r\n<p>-Secure the apartment without disturbing the body or other belongings.</p>\r\n<p>-Local authorities will take control of the situation.</p>\r\n<p>-Local authorities will need the deceased resident''s emergency contact information located in the resident file. They notify the deceased resident''s family.</p>\r\n<p>-VERY IMPORTANT: NO ONE except for the Executor of the Will, not the person with Power of Attorney, is allowed inside the apartment once the apartment has been released by local authorities. The Executor of Will must show proof.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 21:22:17', 1),
(32, 67, 'Gas Leaks', '<p><u><strong>What to do if there is a leak <i>inside</i> the apartment:</strong></u></p>\r\n<p>-If a resident calls to report a gas smell advise the resident to open windows and not light matches or use the gas stove.</p>\r\n<p>-Contact service department or if office is closed contact emergency on-call person.</p>\r\n<p>-Ask resident to step outside the apartment while the service technician does a complete inspection of the apartment.</p>\r\n<p>-If the leak is located make the repair and ask the resident to return to the apartment.</p>\r\n<p>-If the maintenance technician cannot locate the leak, notify the Property Manager and Service Supervisor.</p>\r\n<p>-A decision will be made whether or not the gas company needs to be notified.</p>\r\n<p><u><strong>What to do if there is a leak <i>outside</i> the apartment:</strong></u></p>\r\n<p>-Gas leaks outdoors are much more difficult to detect by smell. Indications of a possible outdoor gas leak include a hissing sound; dirt or water being blown into the air; bubbles on the surface of puddles or ponds; or dead grass or vegetation near a gas line. If any of these are detected, avoid the area and call your gas company or 9-1-1 from a neighbor''s phone.</p>\r\n<p>-If a resident reports a gas smell outside the apartment notify the Property Manager and Service Supervisor.</p>\r\n<p>-If leak cannot be located, contact gas comany regardless if leak was located or not.</p>\r\n<p>-Evacuate all residents.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 21:32:41', 1),
(33, 67, 'Elevator Failure', '<p>-Only qualified personnel should be permitted to correct a malfunction.</p>\r\n<p>-Immediately report failure to Management or Service Supervisor.</p>\r\n<p>-If Service Supervisor is unable to get the people out, contact elevator company immediately.</p>\r\n<p>-Be specific with information: what elevator and building and on what floor did the elevator stop running, is there anyone in the elevator, etc.</p>\r\n<p>-Communication with stranded passengers should be maintained until they are safely evacuated from the elevator. Continually assure them you are working rapidly to free them, that they are safe, caution them not to panic, and warn them not to try to force the elevator door open. Ask them if they require the notification of someone for them. Installed elevator phone systems are especially useful.</p>\r\n<p>-DO NOT evacuate unless the situation is life-threatening. Sudden movemly can be dangerous.</p>\r\n<p>-Remain calm!</p>\r\n<p>-Stay with the people in the elevator until they are free. If trapped for an extended period of time, have Emergency Medicial Personnel on hand.</p>\r\n<p>-Once all people are out, make certain they are alright. Property Manager should meet with each person individually to extend an apology.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 21:41:25', 1),
(34, 67, 'Computer Failure', '<p>\r\n -Do not attempt to operate a visibly damaged computer.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n -If your computer is making an unusual noice, turn it off. There is a good chance it has suffered or will suffer a head crash. The faster it is deactivated, the better the chance for data recovery.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  -Avoid hard exposing the disk drive to environmental hazards by refraining from shaking or removing hard drive and tape covers.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  -Don&#39;t automatically turn to recovery software. If you suspect that you may have lost access to data due to electrical or mechanical failure, software can&#39;t help. Using file recovery utilities on a faulty drive can destroy what was recoverable data.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  -When a drive failure is suspected, turn off the machine. Be sure to call in a computer systems recovery specialist with the proper training and experience. Lost data can become unrecoverable data when un- or under-qualified personnel misuse file recovery utilities, open disk drives, and lack the basic skills necessary to properly maintain and repair computer equipment and data.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  <b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>\r\n _____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  _____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  _____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  _____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  _____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n', '2014-02-14 21:47:38', 1),
(35, 57, 'Crime', '<p><b>If a crime has been committed:</b></p>\r\n<p>- If a crime has been committed, immediately dial 911 from a safe location.</p>\r\n<p>- Never fight, debate, or argue with a person who is out of control or an assailant in a life-threatening situation.</p>\r\n<p>- Try to get a good look at the assailant so you can give a good description to the police. Distinguishing marks such as scars, tattoos, etc. Also the assailant''s height, weight, skin color, hair and eye colors and a description of what the assailant wore is important imformation.</p>\r\n<p>- If there is a crime scene, do not touch anything.</p>\r\n<p>- Encourage witnesses to stay at the scene until police arrive and have the opportunity to question them.</p>\r\n<p>- Contact the property manager.</p>\r\n<p>- Direct all media questions to your company''s media person.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 22:14:20', 1),
(36, 57, 'Bomb Threats', '<p><b>Date Call Received:___________  Time Call Was Received:________</b></p>\r\n<p><b>Time Call Ended:____________</b></p>\r\n<p><b>Employee Taking The Call:_____________________________________</b></p>\r\n<p>Step 1: DO NOT TRANSFER THE CALL.</p>\r\n<p>Step 2: If you have a display phone, note any information shown.</p>\r\n<p>Step 3: Use the pre-determined signal to alert co-workers and of the treat. They will notify police.</p>\r\n<p>Step 4: Do not argue with the caller.</p>\r\n<p>Step 5: Keep the caller on the phone as long as possible. Doing so could allow police to trace the call.</p>\r\n<p>Step 6: Record details of the conversation as noted below immediately following caller hanging up.</p>\r\n<p><b>Ask the following questions:</b></p>\r\n<p>When will the bomb explode?______________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>Where is it now?________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>What does it look it?_____________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>What kind of bomb is it?__________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>What will cause it to explode?______________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>Why are you doing this?__________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>What would you like me to do?_____________________________________________</p>\r\n<p><b>Note the follow details:</b></p>\r\n<p>Male or Female Voice:_____________ Age:__________</p>\r\n<p>Emotional State: ________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>Speech pattern and/or accent:_____________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>Background noises:_____________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>Exact words of the caller:_________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>Additional Comments:____________________________________________________</p>\r\n', '2014-02-14 22:15:32', 1),
(37, 67, 'Crisis Communication', '<p>Success of a communications plan depends on fast and accurate notification of the disaster team and ease of passing on the information.</p>\r\n<p>-Establish a procedure for communication during a disaster.</p>\r\n<p>-Limit communication to emergency procedures ONLY.</p>\r\n<p>-Determine who is authorized to issue communications. Limit the number of authorized personnel.</p>\r\n<p>-Keep all team members emergency phone numbers updated.</p>\r\n<p>-Determine which sources will be used for communication during a disaster.</p>\r\n<p>-Consider use of 2 way radios. Purchase them ahead of time. Spare batteries are essential.</p>\r\n<p>-Battery operated bull horn is useful for mass communication and crowd control.</p>\r\n<p>-Standard announcements should be prepared in advance.</p>\r\n<p>-It is important to utilize a combination of communication resources to advise your residents of potential threats.</p>\r\n<p><u><strong>Resources:</strong></u></p>\r\n<p>Company Website</p>\r\n<p>Twitter</p>\r\n<p>Facebook</p>\r\n<p>Company call center</p>\r\n<p>Text messages</p>\r\n<p>Telephone chain</p>\r\n<p><u><strong>Company Recommendations:</strong></u></p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 22:18:43', 1),
(38, 57, 'Earthquakes', '<p><u><b>During an Earthquake:</b></u></p>\r\n<p>Drop, cover and hold. Move only as far as necessary to reach a safe place.</p>\r\n<p><u><b>If indoors</b></u><b>,</b> stay there. It is safer to stay indoors until the shaking stops and it is safe to exit. When going outdoors, move quickly away from the building to prevent injury from falling debris.</p>\r\n<p><u><b>If outdoors</b></u><b>,</b> find a spot away from buildings, trees, streetlights and power lines and over passes. Drop to the ground and stay there until the shaking stops.</p>\r\n<p><u><b>If in a vehicle</b></u><b>,</b> pull over at a clear location and stop. Stay in the vehicle with seatbelt fastened until the shaking stops.</p>\r\n<p><u><b>If in a high-rise building</b></u><b>,</b> expect the fire alarms and sprinkler systems to go off during an earthquake. Check for and extinguish small fires. DO NOT use elevators.</p>\r\n<p><u><b>If in a coastal area</b></u><b>,</b> move to higher ground. Earthquakes often generate tsunamis.</p>\r\n<p><u><b>If in a mountainous area or near unstable slopes or cliffs</b></u><b>,</b> be alert for falling rock and other debris that could be loosened by the earthquake. Also, watch for landslides that could be triggered by the earthquake.</p>\r\n<p><u><b>Company Recommendations:</b></u></p>\r\n<p>_______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>________________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>________________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 23:21:24', 1),
(39, 57, 'Fires', '<p><u><b>When Fire Breaks Out</b></u></p>\r\n<p>-Regardless of the size of the fire, ALWAYS contact the fire department. Never assume that someone else has called. Then contact the Team Leader to apprise him/her of the situation.</p>\r\n<p>-Team Leader determines if emergency plan activation is necessary.</p>\r\n<p>-If plan is activated, ALL operations shut down to deal with the fire.</p>\r\n<p>-Response Team goes into action.</p>\r\n<p>-Assist emergency fire and police personnel and other emergency management personnel when asked.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>If you are in the building when the fire breaks out and are able to get out:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-Stay calm and do not run because this will fan the flames.</p>\r\n<p>-During your exit, keep in contact with personnel with your two-way radio or cell phone.</p>\r\n<p>-Close as many doors in the hallway or stairwells as possible without endangering yourself.</p>\r\n<p>-Get down on the floor, crawl and use the wall to feel your way out.</p>\r\n<p>-Use handrails as you descend stairs.</p>\r\n<p>-Before opening any doors, test them to see if they are hot by placing the back of your hand carefully on the door. If hot, try to find another way out. If not, slowly open the door.</p>\r\n<p>-If your clothes catch fire, STOP, DROP, ROLL. Cover your face with your hands.</p>\r\n<p>-When outside, move away from the building.</p>\r\n<p><u><b>If you are unable to get out of the building:</b></u></p>\r\n<p>-Stay calm. Do not run. This fans the flames.</p>\r\n<p>-Find a room with a window.</p>\r\n<p>-Use two-way radio or cell phone to notify personnel of your exact location.</p>\r\n<p>-If in a room, open the window to allow air in. Wave something brightly colored out the window.</p>\r\n<p>-Make certain the doors in the room are closed and seal the cracks under the door.</p>\r\n<p>-Cover vents with rags, clothing, towels, newspapers or anything you can find that will do the job.</p>\r\n<p>-If possible use a wet cloth to breath into.</p>\r\n<p>-DO NOT USE ELEVATORS.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n', '2014-02-14 23:21:52', 1),
(40, 57, 'Floods', '<p><b><u>If a Flood is Imminent</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-Contact your immediate supervisor to alert them to the impending situation.</p>\r\n<p>-Team Leader meets with On-Site Emergency Team to review employee assignments.</p>\r\n<p>-Notify residents of impending situation. Bullhorn, knocking on doors, door hangers, telephone calls. Instruct them to remove all belonging from patios and balconies.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>During a Flood</u></b></p>\r\n<p>If you were unable to move to higher ground and are in a building surrounding by flood waters:</p>\r\n<p>-DO NOT ATTEMPT AN ESCAPE. Use your radio or cell phone and call the Team Leader to affirm your location.</p>\r\n<p>-Use no open flames for there may be escaped gas from ruptured lines.</p>\r\n<p>-Shut down power to the buildings.</p>\r\n<p>-In the event flood waters begin entering power source areas try to relocate equipment to higher floors.</p>\r\n<p>Use alternate power sources if they exist.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>If you are in a vehicle</u></b> and water starts to surround the vehicle, DO NOT attempt to drive through the water. Abandon your car and move to higher ground <b><u>immediately</u>.</b></p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n', '2014-02-14 23:22:23', 1),
(41, 57, 'Hurricanes', '<p><b><u>If a Hurricane is Imminent</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-Contact your immediate supervisor and the corporate office and alert them to the impending situation.</p>\r\n<p>-Team Leader meets with On-Site Emergency Team to review individual responsibilities of each team member.</p>\r\n<p>-Activate the Response Team.</p>\r\n<p>-Notify residents of impending situation. Bullhorn, knocking on doors, door hangers, and telephone calls. Instruct them to remove all belongings from patios and balconies.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Hurricane WATCH</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-A Hurricane Watch is issued when there is a threat of hurricane conditions within 24-36 hours.</p>\r\n<p>-Follow company procedures.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>During a Hurricane</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-Refrain from using cell phones, telephones, and radios. Instead send text messages.</p>\r\n<p>-See that all team members are accounted once they are gathered in the pre-designated area. In this area should be the apartment community''s disaster supplies kit and first aid kit.</p>\r\n<p>-Listen to radio for updated information and continually check for text messages.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_______________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 23:23:41', 1),
(42, 57, 'Power Outages', '<p><b><u>Safety Tips in the Event of Power Failure</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-Only use a flashlight for emergency lighting. Never use candles!</p>\r\n<p>-Turn off electrical equipment you were using when the power went out.</p>\r\n<p>-Do not run a generator inside a building or maintenance shop.</p>\r\n<p>-Do not run a generator inside a building or maintenance shop.</p>\r\n<p>-If you use a generator, connect the equipment you want to power directly to the outlets on the generator. Do not connect a generator to a home''s electrical system.</p>\r\n<p>-Listen to local radio and television for updated information.</p>\r\n<p>-Stay alert for down lines. If you see a downed power line, let utility company know immediately.</p>\r\n<p>-Stay away from any downed line. Assume it''s live and dangerous, and warn children to stay away and notify resident. Downed lines do not always spark, burn or arc. Never assume any downed wire is harmless. Objects such as metal fences and water in contact with power lines could be energized and lethal. STAY AWAY.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n', '2014-02-14 23:24:13', 1),
(43, 57, 'Severe Storm', '<p><b><u>Safety Tips in the Event of Power Failure</u></b></p>\r\n<p><u><u> </u></u></p>\r\n<p>-Only use a flashlight for emergency lighting. Never use candles!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>-Turn off electrical equipment you were using when the power went out. -Do not run a generator inside a building or maintenance shop.</p>\r\n<p>-Do not run a generator inside a building or maintenance shop.</p>\r\n<p>-If you use a generator, connect the equipment you want to power directly to the outlets on the generator. Do not connect a generator to a home''s electrical system.</p>\r\n<p>-Listen to local radio and television for updated information.</p>\r\n<p>-Stay alert for down lines. If you see a downed power line, let utility company know immediately. -Stay away from any downed line. Assume it''s live and dangerous, and warn children to stay away and notify resident. Downed lines do not always spark, burn or arc. Never assume any downed wire is harmless. Objects such as metal fences and water in contact with power lines could be energized and lethal. STAY AWAY.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n', '2014-02-14 23:25:12', 1),
(44, 57, 'Work Place Violence', '<p>Although no definite strategy will ever be appropriate for all workplace violence, follow company general procedures for workplace violence. Workplace violence includes any physical assault, threatening behavior, disorderly conduct, any sexual assault, destruction of property, verbal abuse, harassment, telephone or email misuse, stalking, in any location where any employee performs any work-related duty.</p>\r\n<p><u><strong>Preventative Measures Include:</strong></u></p>\r\n<p>-If possible never work alone.</p>\r\n<p>-Establish a code word to be used when in a potential violent situation.</p>\r\n<p>-Always let someone know where you are going and who you are with.</p>\r\n<p>-Carry a cell phone or two-way radio.</p>\r\n<p>-Follow your intuition.</p>\r\n<p>-Learn how to deescalate a distraught person. Be sincere and professional, remain calm, listen, speak in a soft voice, be honest about your limitations, don''t argue, call for help.</p>\r\n<p>-Install good external lighting outside office and maintenance shop areas.</p>\r\n<p>-Consider installing closed-circuit cameras, alarms, two-way mirrors, and card access systems.</p>\r\n<p>-Change-up work practices and staffing patterns.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 23:25:52', 1),
(45, 57, 'Terrorism', '<p>Wherever you are, beware of your surrounding. The very nature of terrorism suggests there may be a little to no warning. Always be alert to suspicious activity and conspicuous or unusual behavior.</p>\r\n<p><u><strong>Acts of terrorism include but are not limited to:</strong></u></p>\r\n<p>-Assassinations</p>\r\n<p>-Kidnappings</p>\r\n<p>-Hijackings</p>\r\n<p>-Bomb scares and bombings</p>\r\n<p>-Dirty bombs</p>\r\n<p>-Cyber attacks (computer based)</p>\r\n<p>-Chemical attacks</p>\r\n<p>-Biological weapons</p>\r\n<p>-Nuclear weapons</p>\r\n<p>-Utility loss or disruption</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 23:27:04', 1),
(46, 57, 'Tornadoes', '<p><b><u>If you find a body:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-Leave the apartment without disturbing the body or other belongings.</p>\r\n<p>-Secure the apartment without disturbing the body or other belongings.</p>\r\n<p>-Local authorities will take control of the situation.</p>\r\n<p>-Local authorities will need the deceased resident''s emergency contact information located in the resident file. They notify the deceased resident''s family.</p>\r\n<p>-VERY IMPORTANT: NO ONE except for the Executor of the Will, not the person with Power of Attorney, is allowed inside the apartment once the apartment has been released by local authorities. The Executor of Will must show proof.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n', '2014-02-14 23:27:28', 1),
(47, 57, 'Resident Death', '<p><b><u>If you find a body:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>-Leave the apartment without disturbing the body or other belongings.</p>\r\n<p>-Secure the apartment without disturbing the body or other belongings.</p>\r\n<p>-Local authorities will take control of the situation.</p>\r\n<p>-Local authorities will need the deceased resident''s emergency contact information located in the resident file. They notify the deceased resident''s family.</p>\r\n<p>-VERY IMPORTANT: NO ONE except for the Executor of the Will, not the person with Power of Attorney, is allowed inside the apartment once the apartment has been released by local authorities. The Executor of Will must show proof.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n', '2014-02-14 23:27:50', 1),
(48, 57, 'Gas Leaks', '<p><u><strong>What to do if there is a leak <i>inside</i> the apartment:</strong></u></p>\r\n<p>-If a resident calls to report a gas smell advise the resident to open windows and not light matches or use the gas stove.</p>\r\n<p>-Contact service department or if office is closed contact emergency on-call person.</p>\r\n<p>-Ask resident to step outside the apartment while the service technician does a complete inspection of the apartment.</p>\r\n<p>-If the leak is located make the repair and ask the resident to return to the apartment.</p>\r\n<p>-If the maintenance technician cannot locate the leak, notify the Property Manager and Service Supervisor.</p>\r\n<p>-A decision will be made whether or not the gas company needs to be notified.</p>\r\n<p><u><strong>What to do if there is a leak <i>outside</i> the apartment:</strong></u></p>\r\n<p>-Gas leaks outdoors are much more difficult to detect by smell. Indications of a possible outdoor gas leak include a hissing sound; dirt or water being blown into the air; bubbles on the surface of puddles or ponds; or dead grass or vegetation near a gas line. If any of these are detected, avoid the area and call your gas company or 9-1-1 from a neighbor''s phone.</p>\r\n<p>-If a resident reports a gas smell outside the apartment notify the Property Manager and Service Supervisor.</p>\r\n<p>-If leak cannot be located, contact gas company regardless if leak was located or not.</p>\r\n<p>-Evacuate all residents.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>', '2014-02-14 23:28:14', 1),
(49, 57, 'Elevator Failure', '<p>-Only qualified personnel should be permitted to correct a malfunction.</p>\r\n<p>-Immediately report failure to Management or Service Supervisor.</p>\r\n<p>-If Service Supervisor is unable to get the people out, contact elevator company immediately.</p>\r\n<p>-Be specific with information: what elevator and building and on what floor did the elevator stop running, is there anyone in the elevator, etc.</p>\r\n<p>-Communication with stranded passengers should be maintained until they are safely evacuated from the elevator. Continually assure them you are working rapidly to free them, that they are safe, caution them not to panic, and warn them not to try to force the elevator door open. Ask them if they require the notification of someone for them. Installed elevator phone systems are especially useful.</p>\r\n<p>-DO NOT evacuate unless the situation is life-threatening. Sudden movements can be dangerous.</p>\r\n<p>-Remain calm!</p>\r\n<p>-Stay with the people in the elevator until they are free. If trapped for an extended period of time, have Emergency Medical Personnel on hand.</p>\r\n<p>-Once all people are out, make certain they are alright. Property Manager should meet with each person individually to extend an apology.</p>\r\n<p><b><u>Company Recommendations:</u></b></p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n<p>______________________________________________________________________</p>\r\n', '2014-02-14 23:28:47', 1);
