(213, 4, 'Elevator Failure', 'Only qualified personnel should be permitted to correct a malfunction.\nImmediately report failure to Management or SErvice Supervisor.\nIf Service Supervisor is unable to get the people out, contact elevator company immediately.\nBe specific with information: what elevator and building and on what floor did the elevator stop running; is there anyone in the elevator, etc.\nCommunication with stranded passengers should be maintained until they are safely evacuated from the elevator. Continually assure them you are working rapidly to free them, that they are safe, caution them not to panic, and warn them not to try to force the elevator door open. Ask them if they require the notification of someone for them. Installed elevator phone systems are especially useful.\nDO NOT evacuate unless the situation is life-threatening. Sudden movement can be dangerous.\nRemain calm!\nStay with the people in the elevator until they are free. If trapped for an extended period of time, have Emergency Medical Personnel on hand.\nOnce all people are out, make certain they are alright. Property Manager should meet with each person individually to extend an apology.', 31, '2011-12-02 00:00:00', 1),
