(279, 5, 'If you are in the building when fire breaks out and are able to get out', 'Stay calm and do not run because this will fan the flames.\nDuring your exit, keep in contact with personnel with your two-way radio or cell phone.\nClose as many doors in the hallway or stairwells as possible without endangering yourself.\nGet down on the floor, crawl and use the wall to feel your way.\nUse handrails as you descend stairs.\nBefore opening any doors, test them tos ee if they are hot by placing the back of your hand carefully on the door. If hot, try to find another way out. If not, slowly open the door.\nIf your clothes catch fire, STOP, DROP, ROLL. Cover your face with your hands.\nWhen outside, move away from the building.', 1, '2012-03-27 10:48:41', 1),
(280, 5, 'If you Are unable to get out of the building', 'Stay calm. Do not run. This fans the flames.\nFind a room with a window.\nUse two-way radio or cell phone to notify personnel of  your exact location.\nIf in a room, open the window to allow air in. Wave something brightly colored out the window.\nMake certain that the doors in the room are closed and seal the cracks under the door.\nCover vents with rags, clothing, towels, newspapers, or anything you can find that will do the job.\nIf possible, use a wet cloth to breath into.\nDO NOT USE ELEVATORS.', 1, '2012-03-27 10:52:24', 1),
