(398, 7, 'What to do if there is a leak inside the apartment?', 'If a resident calls to report a gas smell advise the resident to open windows and not light matches or use the gas stove.\nContact service department or if office is closed contact emergency on-call person.', 1, '2011-10-12 18:38:56', 0),
(399, 7, 'What to do if there is a leak outside the apartment?', 'Gas leaks outdoors are much more difficult to detect by smell. Indications of a possible outdoor gas leak include a hissing sound; dirt or water being blown into the air; bubbles on the surface of puddles or ponds; or dead grass or vegetation near a gas line. If any of these are detected, avoid the area and call your gas company or 9-1-1 from a neighbor''s phone.\nIf a resident reports a gas smell outside the apartment notify the Property Manager and Service Supervisor', 1, '2011-10-12 18:39:21', 0),
