(705, 13, 'Signs to Look For', 'Most obvious are high winds and very large hail.\nSounds like a train is coming.\nTornadoes can be wrapped in heavy rain, which may limit visibility. But because tornadoes are associated with powerful updrafts, rain does not always fall in or near tornadoes.\nTornadoes may appear nearly transparent until they pick up dust and debris. In this case, debris such as branches or leaves being pulled upwards is a clue.\nAn obvious funnel-shaped cloud that is rotating.\nSickly greenish or greenish black sky.\nA strange quiet that occurs within or shortly after a thunderstorm.\nClouds moving very fast.\nDebris dropping from sky', 1, '2011-10-13 15:28:01', 1),
(706, 13, 'If Outdoors', 'If possible, get inside a building.\nIf shelter is not available or there is no time to get indoors, lie in a ditch or low-lying area or crouch near a strong building. Be aware of the potential for flooding.\nUse arms to protect head and neck.', 1, '2011-10-13 15:28:25', 1),
(707, 13, 'If in a vehicle', 'Never try to out-drive a tornado in a car or trucks.\nGet out of the vehicle immediately and take shelter in a nearby building.\nIf there is no time to get indoors, get out of the vehicle and lie in a ditch or low-lying area away from the vehicle.', 12, '2011-10-23 00:00:00', 1),
