(23, 'Proceed to nearest exit and head towards Jackson Road', 'See attached NJ evacuation map.', 'N/A', 41, 44, '2012-10-25 00:57:45', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 1),
(24, 'In the event that Shore 1 and /or the city of Jersey City declares an evacuation, please follow the directions on the attached map of Hudson County Coastal Evacuation Routes.\r\n\r\nIf the building is unaffected, please use al point and methods of egress to exit the building in an orderly fashion. Use elevators and stairs to get to the ground floor to exit building.\r\n\r\nIn the event that Shore 1 is affected by the emergency, you may have to use stairs to exit building. Please proceed in an orderly fashion to the nearest exit stairs to walk to ground level and exit building.\r\n', 'The Primary Evacuation Route is Rte. 495 W to the New Jersey Turnpike and proceed either North or South depending on the emergency. An additional option would be to exit at Rte 3, and transit to the East Rutherford area. (FOLLOW the  Blue Dot to safety)', 'The Secondary Evacuation Rte is to make your way to Rte. 139 W to connect with Routes 1/9 towards the NJ Turnpike. Once on the Turnpike look for evacuation information on local radio and signage on the turnpike. (FOLLOW  the Blue Dot to safety)', 45, 51, '2013-02-09 00:44:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 1),
(25, 'Immediately evacuate the the building using the shortest but safest route. If there is a smell of smoke or if you see smoke, use an alternative escape route which consists of either exiting through the front or back door exit located on the 1st Floor. Once out of the building all residents must go to a safe area outside away from the building.', 'All residents of Poplar Street will exit the apartment, using the exit signs located on each floor near the stairs, as guidance. This will direct them to the front and back door exit located on the 1st Floor. They must use the shortest but safest route. \r\nAll residents of Ogden Street will exit the apartment, using the exit signs located on each floor near the stairs, as guidance. This will direct them to the front and back door exit located on the 1st Floor. They must use the shortest but safest route.', 'All residents of both Poplar and Ogden will exit through the back door of each building. They will then walk through the back and exit through the courtyard which will place all residents on Ogden Street side. they will then be instructed to move as far away as possible from the building.\r\nSee Attached Floor Plans', 55, 70, '2013-10-02 22:47:37', '2013-10-02 22:47:37', 1),
(26, 'Leave affected site in an orderly fashion.\r\nMeet at Management Office or Community Room for a head count and instructions.', 'Any street that is possible away from danger.', 'Stay put wait for help only if safe.', 55, 77, '2013-10-02 23:03:49', '2013-10-02 23:03:49', 1),
(27, 'Each floor captain check all units are empty and direct tenants to nearest stairwell. \r\nOnce outside of building all tenants and staff gather outside 192 E Indiana Ave and report to head duty monitor.', 'Floors 3-6 to front of building exit by stairs to courtyard.\r\nFloors 3-6 to rear of building exit by stairs to street.\r\nFloors LL-2 to front of building exit by stairs to Main entrance.\r\nFloors LL-2 to rear of building exit by stairs to street.\r\n*Tenants on lower level use exit to courtyard if necessary.*', 'NA', 55, 76, '2013-10-02 23:19:35', '2013-10-02 23:19:35', 1),
