(162, 'Notify resident and their family, or personnel of responsibility.\r\n\r\nExit building using closest, safest exit. Continue to command center.', 'East on Route 33, Greenwood Avenue away from Delaware River.', 'North or South on US-1', 305, 425, '2014-03-31 19:18:17', '2014-03-31 19:18:17', 1),
(163, 'Notify resident and their family, or personnel of responsibility.\r\n\r\nExit building using closest, safest exit. Continue to command center.', 'East on Route 33, Greenwood Avenue away from Delaware River.', 'North or South on US-1', 305, 426, '2014-03-31 19:19:52', '2014-03-31 19:19:52', 1),
(164, 'The residents should exit their apartments, continue down the stairs (DO NOT USE ELEVATORS) and proceed to exit the building. Residents are to meet at the office on Skiles Blvd. If that location is affected by the incident, proceed to the gated entrance on Skiles Blvd. Lincoln staff should perform a headcount and communicate with residents as appropriate using company guidelines for the correct message. Please remember to collect contact information, including phone numbers.\r\nIf evacuated, the staff should contact their regional manager for support and a communication plan.', 'If evacuation is required, temporary shelter will be provided in West Chester area schools. Chester county will provide an emergency route on an as needed basis. ', 'TBD', 304, 427, '2014-04-08 00:59:36', '2014-04-08 00:59:36', 1),
(165, 'The residents should exit their apartments, continue down the stairs and proceed o the club house. Lincoln staff should perform a headcount and communicate with residents as appropriate using company guidelines for the correct message. \r\nIf evacuated, the staff should contact their regional manager for support and communication plan. ', 'If an evacuation is required, temporary shelter will be provided in West Chester area schools. Chester county will provide an emergency route on an as needed basis. ', 'TBD', 304, 428, '2014-04-08 01:03:08', '2014-04-08 01:03:08', 1),
(166, 'Proceed to nearest stairwell and exit building- DO NOT USE ELEVATORS', 'See attached York County evacuation map', 'TBD', 68, 151, '2014-04-08 21:38:02', '2014-04-08 21:38:02', 1),
(167, 'All residents in units 01-10 will use the stairwell to the parking lot and meet everyone in front of the building. All residents in units 11-17 will use the stairwell to the lobby and exit the lobby doors to the front of the building. ', 'Lobby entrance', 'Parking lot entrance', 68, 433, '2014-04-09 18:16:22', '2014-04-09 18:16:22', 1),
(168, 'To be determined.', 'Gloucester County', 'To be determined.', 68, 157, '2014-04-10 20:21:17', '2014-04-10 20:21:17', 1),
(169, 'All residents are required to exit building through front door.', 'Through basement, back door.', 'TBD', 68, 159, '2014-04-10 23:40:11', '2014-04-10 23:40:11', 1),
(170, 'At the sound of emergency alarm system, all residents must use closest stairwell and assemble in front of the building- Allegheny Avenue.', 'Main stairwell near elevator and the exits at the end of each hallway.', '1st St. or 16th St. ', 68, 160, '2014-04-11 01:01:08', '2014-04-11 01:01:08', 1),
(171, 'As alarm sounds the residents will need to proceed to the nearest evacuation route. Responsible party will need to notify emergency personnel of the handicap units. 201-205-301-305-401-405. Responsible party will need to check common areas such as club room, fitness room, garden room, community room, laundry room and bathrooms.', '1st floor if fire is in front- will need to exit building from rear door.\r\n2nd floor will proceed down south stairwell steps and exit building on south end.\r\n3rd floor will proceed down the stairwell steps and exit building on south end.\r\n4th floor will proceed down nearest steps and exit building on south end.', '1st floor will exit north end exit or through the parking garage.\r\n2nd floor will proceed to north end stairwell and exit stairwell exit.\r\n3rd floor will proceed to north end stairwell and exit to stairwell exit.\r\n4th floor will proceed to north end stairwell and exit to stairwell exit.', 68, 161, '2014-04-11 01:13:37', '2014-04-11 01:13:37', 1),
(172, 'Proceed to closest fire tower.', 'Proceed toward Lenola Rd. and travel North or South to get away from buildings.', 'To be determined. ', 68, 162, '2014-04-11 18:33:39', '2014-04-11 18:33:39', 1),
(173, 'Follow all exit signs using stairs to exit building.', 'To be determined', 'To be determined', 68, 163, '2014-04-11 19:04:20', '2014-04-11 19:04:20', 1),
(174, 'The emergency alarm system in the buildings will sound and management will alert residents from outside the lobby that everyone must vacate the property. They will use the steps only.', 'Stairways at main entrance and all fire emergency routes at the back and sides of the buildings.', '1st st or 16th st', 68, 164, '2014-04-11 19:23:25', '2014-04-11 19:23:25', 1),
(175, 'Exit your apartment closing the door behind you and use the stairs to proceed to the assembly point on the grass along side Denow Rd. or to the parking lot of the Learning Center Daycare Center at 795 Denow Rd, which is next to Hopewell Garden. Residents unable to use the stairs are to gather in the sitting room(s) closest to his or her apartment. Sitting rooms are located on each floor at the East and West sides of the buildings (near elevators). They should wait for the Fire Department personnel to arrive and escort them out of the building. If a stairwell has been compromised by smoke or fire, they should not use it but go to the next available stairwell. If smoke or fire is encountered along the way, they should proceed to the sitting room on the opposite end of their floor. No one should return to the building until an authorized Management representative or the Fire Department has declared it safe to do so. ', 'To be determined.', 'To be determined. ', 68, 167, '2014-04-11 20:57:41', '2014-04-11 20:57:41', 1),
(176, 'Stairwell on each floor.', 'Each floor is to evacuate by way of back stairwell that leads to outside grounds.', 'Each floor is to evacuate by way of back stairwell that leads to outside grounds.', 68, 168, '2014-04-11 23:17:37', '2014-04-11 23:17:37', 1),
(177, '1. Everyone leaves building safely.\r\n2. A procedure to safely evacuate individuals who cannot negotiate stairs is in place.\r\n3. Building occupants are account for after an emergency evacuation.\r\n4. Personnel are selected among building occupants, with function to ensure plan objective are met.', 'Follow the news and instruction for evacuation route depends on the nature of the disaster.', 'For fire and earthquake: everybody has to be out of the buildings.\r\n\r\nFlood and hurricanes: evacuate if instructed by your local township. Otherwise remain in your apartment. ', 68, 169, '2014-04-11 23:32:05', '2014-04-11 23:32:05', 1),
(178, 'Emergency Management Preparedness Plan from county and fire department', 'To be determined.', 'To be determined.', 68, 171, '2014-04-12 00:02:59', '2014-04-12 00:02:59', 1),
(179, 'Emergency management preparedness plan from county and fire departments. Stay in place policy.', 'Stairwell to 1st floor from lobby to out through main door or through exit doors on either side or out the community room door. ', 'To be determined.', 68, 173, '2014-04-14 21:01:12', '2014-04-14 21:01:12', 1),
(180, 'When the fire alarm sounds, the staff person sitting at the front desk must call 911 before evacuating the building and then call the manager.', 'Proceed to the fire escape and leave building. Use the exit leading onto the outside landing and into the fire exit.', 'As a last option, go to the roof.', 68, 175, '2014-04-14 23:24:33', '2014-04-14 23:24:33', 1),
(181, 'Follow coastal evacuation route- see attached map.', 'Coastal Evacuation route ', 'Atlantic City Expressway', 68, 177, '2014-04-15 19:15:07', '2014-04-15 19:15:07', 1),
(182, 'All tenants are to report downstairs and gather in the lobby area. In the event of a building emergency, the elevator is designed to take the tenants downstairs to the first floor. Then everyone should meet in the lobby area.', 'Everyone proceed downstairs by way of elevator if there is NO fire. Exit the building from the front or rear exit doors by the stairwell (end of the hallway). Tenants should head to the top of the parking lot.', 'Everyone should take the stairs/elevators if there is no fire. Exit the building from the entrance, rear emergency doors (located at the first floor''s front and rear stairwell). Go across the street to Blandenwood Condominiums.', 68, 178, '2014-04-15 20:44:48', '2014-04-15 20:44:48', 1),
(183, 'Per emergency team at West New York.', 'To be determined.', 'To be determined.', 68, 179, '2014-04-15 21:19:55', '2014-04-15 21:19:55', 1),
(184, 'Follow all exit signs using stairs to exit building.', 'Out toward Compton Ave.', 'Out toward Lee Street into Park. ', 68, 180, '2014-04-15 23:56:17', '2014-04-15 23:56:17', 1),
(185, 'Pull alarms to notify residents of an emergency. Escort off property.', 'Beverly Drive- left on Port Capital Dr. and then across street to empty lot.', 'Beverly Drive- right on Port Capital towards gated community. ', 68, 182, '2014-04-16 00:38:43', '2014-04-16 00:38:43', 1),
(186, 'OEM route plan to- Pathmark- Bagel Place- Lincoln/Eisenhower School\r\nAdvise pending each event\r\nPre-designated shelters', 'To be determined', 'To be determined', 68, 183, '2014-04-16 01:14:53', '2014-04-16 01:14:53', 1),
(187, 'Exit individual unit and proceed to closest stairwell. Exit building through side doors.', 'to be determined', 'to be determined', 302, 424, '2014-04-16 21:05:12', '2014-04-16 21:05:12', 1),
(188, 'Jersey City Fire department code', 'To be determined', 'To be determined', 68, 185, '2014-04-17 17:44:21', '2014-04-17 17:44:21', 1),
(189, 'To be determined.', 'Winterborn Lane to Dykes Road. Right on Dykes. Right on South Division. Left on Milford. Right on 13 North.', 'Winterborn Lane to Dykes Road. Left on Dykes. Left on Robbins. Right on Snow Hill Rd.- Take 13 Bypass North', 68, 186, '2014-04-17 18:02:52', '2014-04-17 18:02:52', 1),
(190, 'Pull keys- go to handicap united and 123 deaf person. Go door to door to alert residents. Instruct to go to designated location. Contact emergency services.', 'See attached', 'To be determined. ', 68, 187, '2014-04-17 18:22:36', '2014-04-17 18:22:36', 1),
(191, 'When an alarm is transmitted and sounded, turn off stove. Leave at once. Close apartment door, but do not lock and proceed to fire exit stair tower. Exit the building. Do not use elevators. Feel the door that leads from your apartment to corridor before opening. If it is hot or smoke seeping in, do not open. Seal any crack. Call 911 and tell them your address. If it''s cool, open cautiously- if corridor is clear, proceed to fire exit. Anyone who is disabled, should proceed to fire stairtower and stand fast on one side of stairway in single file until assistance is available. Be sure to keep fire doors closed so smoke can not enter stairtower.', 'From fire exit, east tower- down steps to first floor. Exit through side door and out to Carpenter St. turn left to Bonsall.', 'Fire fire exit, west tower- exit on 2nd floor and out to back of building. Turn right to parking lot then exit to Carpenter St. then left to Bonsall.', 68, 190, '2014-04-17 19:08:21', '2014-04-17 19:08:21', 1),
(192, 'When the alarm goes off, make the announcement to please evacuate the building immediately. The elevators automatically come down to the first floor.', 'Leave by way of exit door- exit outside to the streets and parking areas.', 'To be determined. ', 68, 191, '2014-04-17 19:21:23', '2014-04-17 19:21:23', 1),
(193, 'Using stairs and hallways, exit building. Proceed to designated command/resident area.', 'See attached NJ evacuation route map.', 'To be determined. ', 68, 193, '2014-04-17 19:38:11', '2014-04-17 19:38:11', 1),
(194, 'Leave the apartment immediately closing apartment door firmly behind you. Please DO NOT LOCK apartment just exit the building. PULL FIRE ALARM NEAREST TO YOU. Go to a safe place away from the building and call 911 for police, fire and ambulance. Call office/answering service if during office hours (8am-5pm) 617-442-0281 & leave a detailed message, name, apartment number and nature of the emergency. Call building security on duty if after office hours (5pm-8am) 617-427-5196 & leave a detailed message, name, apartment number and nature of the emergency. DO NOT ATTEMPT TO PUT OUT FIRE  YOURSELF, SAVE YOUR PROPERTY OR RETURN TO THE BUILDING UNTIL ADVISED BY THE FIRE DEPARTMENT. Knock on neighbors doors only on your floor as you make your way to the staircase if safe to do so assisting the elderly or sick.', 'Walk up #24 through walk up #30, please exit the apartment and assemble at the designated meeting point at the upper level parking lot. Town houses #26 through #40, please exit the apartment and assemble at the designated meeting point at the upper level parking lot. Apts 204-215, 301-315, 401-415. 501-515, 601-615, 701-711, please exit through the east front stairs to the east front door way orderly assisting others where possible. Apts 216-229, 316-329, 416-429, 516-529, 616-629, 712-721, please exit through the west rear stairs to the west rear door way orderly assisting others where possible. All residents are to assemble at the upper level parking lot for a head count immediately. Please stay put there unless otherwise instructed.', 'To be determined.', 320, 435, '2014-04-25 21:19:45', '2014-04-25 21:19:45', 1),
(195, 'All residents to be evacuated rear stairways and escorted either to the rear of property parking lot or tennis courts- conditions permitting. Residents are directed to meet at the designated command center.', 'See Palm Beach County evacuate route map.', 'To be determined.', 37, 437, '2014-05-03 00:52:53', '2014-05-03 00:52:53', 1),
(196, 'Residents are directed to follow exit signs out of the front door. Residents are directed to meet at the designated resident command center.', 'See Broward County evacuation route map.', 'To be determined.', 37, 438, '2014-05-06 23:40:30', '2014-05-06 23:40:30', 1),
(197, 'All residents to be evacuated rear stairways and escorted either to the rear of property parking lot or tennis courts- conditions permitting. Residents are directed to meet at the designated resident command center.', 'See Broward County evacuation route map', 'To be determined', 37, 439, '2014-05-07 20:27:24', '2014-05-07 20:27:24', 1),
(198, 'All residents to be evacuated rear stairways and escorted either to the rear of the property parking lot or tennis courts- conditions permitting. Residents are directed to meet at the designated resident command center.', 'See Broward County Evacuation route map.', 'To be determined. ', 37, 440, '2014-05-08 00:25:25', '2014-05-08 00:25:25', 1),
