(201, 109, 35, 'Boiler Shut Down Switch', 'Use this switch in emergencies only. ', '0336407001400175445.JPG', 1),
(202, 109, 35, 'Boiler controls', 'All 5 boiler controls and disconnects located to the left of the room on the right hand side. You should use these disconnects when servicing any of the boilers and/or the circulating pumps. Note: When performing service to this equipment you should always use proper Lock-out Tag-out procedures. Material on these procedures can be found in the maintenance shop at the Safety Center.', '0205621001400175633.JPG', 1),
(203, 109, 35, 'Techmar Controls', 'To the left of the 5 pump/boiler disconnects and controls are the Techmar boiler/heating loop controls and disconnects', '0344185001400181616.JPG', 1),
(204, 109, 35, 'Heating loop pump Controls ', 'Heating loop pump controls and disconnects (residential and commercial).', '0345151001400181616.JPG', 1),
(205, 109, 35, 'Main Sprinkler Valve & Back-flow Preventer', 'To the right of the Techmar controls, is the main fire sprinkler valve and back-flow preventer. This valve shuts down the entire sprinkler water supply. If this vale is shut off, an alarm will sound and the master box will trip; alerting the Cambridge Fire Department. Note: sprinkler pipes should be painted red and labeled "Fire Sprinkler."', '0345967001400181616.JPG', 1),
(206, 109, 35, 'Main Sprinkler Valve & Back-flow Preventer', 'To the right of the Techmar controls, is the main fire sprinkler valve and back-flow preventer. This valve shuts down the entire sprinkler water supply. If this vale is shut off, an alarm will sound and the master box will trip; alerting the Cambridge Fire Department. Note: sprinkler pipes should be painted red and labeled "Fire Sprinkler."', '0346760001400181616.JPG', 1),
(207, 109, 35, 'Gas Shut off Valve and Meters', 'To the right of the main sprinkler valve/back-flow preventer, and along the exterior wall you will find the property''s gas shut-off valves and meters.', '0347568001400181616.JPG', 1),
(208, 109, 35, 'Gas Shut off Valve and Meters', 'To the right of the main sprinkler valve/back-flow preventer, and along the exterior wall you will find the property''s gas shut-off valves and meters.', '0348359001400181616.JPG', 1),
(209, 109, 35, 'View of Water Main and Pumps', 'The view looking forwards toward the building''s water main and pumps.', '0349143001400181616.JPG', 1),
(210, 109, 35, 'Heating Loop Pumps', '2 pumps are for the residential heating loop (these pumps provide heating water to all the property''s apartments). Only 1 pump is necessary to perform this task. The second pump is for back up purposes. Each month the pumps should be alternated and PM''d for optimum operations. The third heating loop pump is the primary pump that provides heating water to the commercial suites. This pump should be PM''d monthly and observed during daily readings.', '0349919001400181616.JPG', 1),
(211, 109, 35, 'Heating Loop Pumps', '2 pumps are for the residential heating loop (these pumps provide heating water to all the property''s apartments). Only 1 pump is necessary to perform this task. The second pump is for back up purposes. Each month the pumps should be alternated and PM''d for optimum operations. The third heating loop pump is the primary pump that provides heating water to the commercial suites. This pump should be PM''d monthly and observed during daily readings.', '0350728001400181616.JPG', 1),
(212, 109, 35, '2 Cooling Tower Pumps (green) & 2 Heating Loop Pumps (gold)', 'To the right of the heating loop pumps are 5 Lochinvar Condensing Boilers. These boilers provide heat and DHW (domestic hot water) for the entire property. At the left of the boilers are commercial loop pumps. 2 Cooling Tower pumps and two Heat Loop pumps for the various heat pump units around the property. Only 1 pump each is necessary for proper operation. The additional pumps are for back-up purposes, and should be alternated and PM''d monthly for optimum operational life. Daily readings should be done to ensure the system is working properly. See HVAC log for proper temperature and pressure settings. Note: the Cooling Tower is located on the roof of the 810 building at the front of the property. The pump disconnects and controls are located just above the pumps near the commercial heating loop pump.', '0351553001400181616.JPG', 1),
(213, 109, 35, 'Disconnects/Controls for the Cooling Tower & Heating loop pumps.', 'To the right of the heating loop pumps are 5 Lochinvar Condensing Boilers. These boilers provide heat and DHW (domestic hot water) for the entire property. At the left of the boilers are commercial loop pumps. 2 Cooling Tower pumps and two Heat Loop pumps for the various heat pump units around the property. Only 1 pump each is necessary for proper operation. The additional pumps are for back-up purposes, and should be alternated and PM''d monthly for optimum operational life. Daily readings should be done to ensure the system is working properly. See HVAC log for proper temperature and pressure settings. Note: the Cooling Tower is located on the roof of the 810 building at the front of the property. The pump disconnects and controls are located just above the pumps near the commercial heating loop pump.', '0352382001400181616.JPG', 1),
(214, 109, 35, 'Additional Pump Sequencer & Breakers', 'To the right of the heating loop pumps are 5 Lochinvar Condensing Boilers. These boilers provide heat and DHW (domestic hot water) for the entire property. At the left of the boilers are commercial loop pumps. 2 Cooling Tower pumps and two Heat Loop pumps for the various heat pump units around the property. Only 1 pump each is necessary for proper operation. The additional pumps are for back-up purposes, and should be alternated and PM''d monthly for optimum operational life. Daily readings should be done to ensure the system is working properly. See HVAC log for proper temperature and pressure settings. Note: the Cooling Tower is located on the roof of the 810 building at the front of the property. The pump disconnects and controls are located just above the pumps near the commercial heating loop pump.', '0353216001400181616.JPG', 1),
(215, 109, 35, 'Additional Pump Sequencer & Breakers', 'To the right of the heating loop pumps are 5 Lochinvar Condensing Boilers. These boilers provide heat and DHW (domestic hot water) for the entire property. At the left of the boilers are commercial loop pumps. 2 Cooling Tower pumps and two Heat Loop pumps for the various heat pump units around the property. Only 1 pump each is necessary for proper operation. The additional pumps are for back-up purposes, and should be alternated and PM''d monthly for optimum operational life. Daily readings should be done to ensure the system is working properly. See HVAC log for proper temperature and pressure settings. Note: the Cooling Tower is located on the roof of the 810 building at the front of the property. The pump disconnects and controls are located just above the pumps near the commercial heating loop pump.', '0354030001400181616.JPG', 1),
(216, 109, 35, 'Main water shut off valves', 'To the right of the commercial loop pumps is the property''s water main. At the water main location are the water meter and main shut of valves. These valves control all water throughout the property. Flanking both sides of the water main are the domestic water booster pumps. These pumps provide water to the entire property. Only 1 pump is necessary for this task. The second pump is for back-up purposes, and should be alternated and PM''d monthly for optimum operational life. Each pump is operated through a VFD ( variable frequency drive). This drive enables the pump to operate more efficiently, by increasing and decreasing the pump speed due to property water demand. Faster pump speed = more demand. Slower pump speed = less demand. The booster pump disconnects are located beneath the VFD''s. ', '0354854001400181616.JPG', 1),
(217, 109, 35, 'Main Water Meter', 'To the right of the commercial loop pumps is the property''s water main. At the water main location are the water meter and main shut of valves. These valves control all water throughout the property. Flanking both sides of the water main are the domestic water booster pumps. These pumps provide water to the entire property. Only 1 pump is necessary for this task. The second pump is for back-up purposes, and should be alternated and PM''d monthly for optimum operational life. Each pump is operated through a VFD ( variable frequency drive). This drive enables the pump to operate more efficiently, by increasing and decreasing the pump speed due to property water demand. Faster pump speed = more demand. Slower pump speed = less demand. The booster pump disconnects are located beneath the VFD''s. ', '0355722001400181616.JPG', 1),
(218, 109, 35, 'Domestic Water Booster Pumps', 'To the right of the commercial loop pumps is the property''s water main. At the water main location are the water meter and main shut of valves. These valves control all water throughout the property. Flanking both sides of the water main are the domestic water booster pumps. These pumps provide water to the entire property. Only 1 pump is necessary for this task. The second pump is for back-up purposes, and should be alternated and PM''d monthly for optimum operational life. Each pump is operated through a VFD ( variable frequency drive). This drive enables the pump to operate more efficiently, by increasing and decreasing the pump speed due to property water demand. Faster pump speed = more demand. Slower pump speed = less demand. The booster pump disconnects are located beneath the VFD''s. ', '0356554001400181616.JPG', 1),
(219, 109, 35, 'BFD & Booster Pump Disconnects', 'To the right of the commercial loop pumps is the property''s water main. At the water main location are the water meter and main shut of valves. These valves control all water throughout the property. Flanking both sides of the water main are the domestic water booster pumps. These pumps provide water to the entire property. Only 1 pump is necessary for this task. The second pump is for back-up purposes, and should be alternated and PM''d monthly for optimum operational life. Each pump is operated through a VFD ( variable frequency drive). This drive enables the pump to operate more efficiently, by increasing and decreasing the pump speed due to property water demand. Faster pump speed = more demand. Slower pump speed = less demand. The booster pump disconnects are located beneath the VFD''s. ', '0357858001400181616.JPG', 1),
(220, 109, 35, '810/812 Building Cold Water Shut off Valve', 'Cold water shut off valve for the 810/812 building is located just above the water main and booster pumps.', '0358780001400181616.JPG', 1),
(221, 109, 35, '808 Building Cold Water Shut off Valve', 'The cold water shut off valve for the 808 building is located at the right of the entrance door, above a set of PRV''s (pressure reducing valve).', '0359673001400181616.JPG', 1),
(222, 109, 35, 'DHW Pressure Reducing Valve & Cold Water Pressure Reducing Valve ', 'Top valve is the hot water and bottom is the cold water.\r\n\r\nAt the same location as the 808 building cold water shut off (right of the entrance door) is the property''s domestic hot and cold water PRV''s. These valves regulate the pressure of the water that is distributed to the property. The pressure going into the valves are generally at 115 to 120 psi, they are reduced to approx. 70-80 psi. ', '0360560001400181616.JPG', 1),
(223, 109, 35, 'Building DWH Shut off Vavle', 'Above, and to the right of the Pressure Reducing Valves is the 810/812 building DHW shut off valve. This valve will shut only the hot water in the 810 & 812 building. ', '0340723001400243645.JPG', 1),
(224, 109, 35, '808 Building DHW Shut off Valve', 'To the right of the Pressure Reducing Valves and along the wall next to the entrance door are the 808 DHW shut off valve. ', '0341800001400243645.JPG', 1),
